1. Authentication APIs
Register User

Endpoint

POST /api/auth/register

Request Body

{
 "name": "Madhav Gill",
 "email": "madhav@gmail.com",
 "password": "123456"
}

Response

{
 "message": "User registered successfully"
}
Login User

Endpoint

POST /api/auth/login

Request Body

{
 "email": "madhav@gmail.com",
 "password": "123456"
}

Response

{
 "token": "jwt_token_here",
 "user": {
   "id": "12345",
   "name": "Madhav Gill"
 }
}

Frontend must store:

token

Used for authenticated requests.

2. Portfolio APIs

These APIs manage user investments.

Add Stock to Portfolio

Endpoint

POST /api/portfolio/add

Headers

Authorization: Bearer <token>

Request Body

{
 "stockSymbol": "RELIANCE",
 "quantity": 10,
 "buyPrice": 2500
}

Response

{
 "message": "Stock added successfully"
}
Get User Portfolio

Endpoint

GET /api/portfolio

Headers

Authorization: Bearer <token>

Response

{
 "totalInvestment": 25000,
 "totalStocks": 3,
 "stocks": [
   {
     "symbol": "RELIANCE",
     "quantity": 10,
     "sector": "Energy",
     "currentValue": 12000
   },
   {
     "symbol": "TCS",
     "quantity": 5,
     "sector": "IT",
     "currentValue": 8000
   }
 ]
}

Frontend uses this data for:

portfolio table

portfolio summary card

3. Sector Allocation API

Used for portfolio diversification visualization.

Get Sector Distribution

Endpoint

GET /api/portfolio/sectors

Headers

Authorization: Bearer <token>

Response

{
 "Banking": 35,
 "IT": 25,
 "Energy": 20,
 "Pharma": 10,
 "FMCG": 10
}

Frontend uses this response for:

sector pie chart

diversification visualization

4. Portfolio Analysis API

This API triggers AI analysis.

Analyze Portfolio

Endpoint

POST /api/analysis/portfolio

Headers

Authorization: Bearer <token>

Response

{
 "diversificationScore": 68,
 "riskScore": 55,
 "portfolioHealth": 72,
 "recommendations": [
   "Reduce banking exposure",
   "Add pharmaceutical stocks",
   "Consider index ETFs for diversification"
 ]
}

Frontend displays:

risk score

diversification score

AI recommendation panel

5. Advisor APIs

These APIs allow users to connect with advisors.

Get Advisors

Endpoint

GET /api/advisors

Response

[
 {
   "id": "1",
   "name": "Rahul Sharma",
   "experience": "10 years",
   "rating": 4.8,
   "specialization": "Equity Investment"
 },
 {
   "id": "2",
   "name": "Neha Gupta",
   "experience": "8 years",
   "rating": 4.6,
   "specialization": "Portfolio Management"
 }
]

Frontend shows advisor list.

Book Advisor Consultation

Endpoint

POST /api/advisor/book

Headers

Authorization: Bearer <token>

Request Body

{
 "advisorId": "1",
 "date": "2026-04-10",
 "time": "15:00"
}

Response

{
 "message": "Consultation booked successfully"
}

Frontend shows booking confirmation.

6. API Authentication Flow

All protected APIs require:

Authorization: Bearer <JWT_TOKEN>

Example request header:

Authorization: Bearer eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9
7. API Groups Overview
API Group	Purpose
Auth APIs	Login & registration
Portfolio APIs	Manage investments
Sector APIs	Portfolio breakdown
Analysis APIs	AI portfolio insights
Advisor APIs	Financial consultation
8. API Communication Flow

Frontend communication pattern:

User Action
     ↓
React Component
     ↓
Axios API Call
     ↓
Backend API
     ↓
JSON Response
     ↓
Update UI



